    <div style=3D"display:none;">Meeting Purpose

Discuss pricing and partnership model between Aleph and CounselFi for scala=
ble financial services.

Key Takeaways

  - Aleph offers tiered pricing: ~$30/mo for bookkeeping clients, higher fo=
r strategic finance services
  - CounselFi sees value in starting clients with basic integration, then u=
pselling more advanced features
  - Aleph to provide detailed pricing spreadsheet and mock implementation p=
lan by end of day
  - Both parties align on the potential for mutually beneficial, scalable p=
artnership

Topics

CounselFi's Business Model and Needs

  - 40-50 client business, aiming for rapid growth over next 3 years
  - Offers tiered services: bookkeeping, strategic finance, and a middle ti=
er
  - Seeks tools to elevate FP&amp;A capabilities and complement existing st=
ack (e.g., Keeper)
